Name: Digital Penetration: Finding Your Audience in 2015
Description: The comedy landscape has undergone tremendous changes in the last ten years, not just with the advent of Twitter, Podcast Networks, Vine, Tumblr, YouTube, Instagram and Facebook, but with how the art form is produced and shared with a broad audience. Digital media has opened up countless avenues for comedians to expand their reach and refine their voice. What are some of the most valuable methods for getting your work out there and building an audience? What are the potential pitfalls of this Brave New World? In this panel discussion, performers are joined by producers and industry reps for an in depth discussion on how digital media and unconventional distribution can assist, and possibly improve, today's generation of comics and writers.

Name: Sexpot Comedy Presents: Uncalled Four
Description: Performing stand-up to start the show, each comic has a chance to win over the crowd by giving them a glimpse into their psyche. When posed ridiculous questions generated by those in attendance, comedians draw from a deck of their own creation to give the most twisted and hilarious answers.

Name: Let's Do It With Bri Pruett!
Description: Local sex advice columnist and comedy rockstar Bri Pruett hosts this night of sexy humor featuring comics from all over the country.

Name: In the Heath of the Night with Veronica Heath
Description: Always effervescent, Portland's Veronica Heath hosts this stand-up show featuring festival favorites and exciting new faces.

Name: Grand Illusions
Description: Head on down to My Father's Place on Grand Ave. for this stand-up showcase featuring a mix of Bridgetown newbies and festival favorites.

Name: Probably Science
Description: The hit podcast in which professional comedians who are also incompetent scientists take you through this week in science. Incompetently. Featuring Matt Kirshen (Jimmy Fallon, Craig Ferguson, Nerdist, Last Comic Standing) and Andy Wood (Jason Nash Is Married, MOCKpocalypse), with special guests from the world of science and comedy

Name: Sex Nerd Sandra
Description: Lighthearted, sex-positive and curiosity driven, this podcast brilliantly gives comedians ample material for laughs.

Name: Dr. Katz, Professional Therapist: a 20th Anniversary Celebration
Description: Join Jonathan Katz and special guests for a live production of the groundbreaking animated show Dr. Katz, Professional Therapist. Tickets

Name: The Dork Forest
Description: Jackie Kashian discusses favorite obsessions with the obsessed. Video games, Comic Books, Birdwatching. How deep in the dork forest are you? Celebrate it and f*&%$, make it your own!

Name: TV Guidance Counselor
Description: Hosted by Boston comedian Ken Reid, TV Guidance Counselor is a new podcast about old TV. The premise is, Ken owns every TV Guide from 1980-1995 or so. Someone picks a random TV Guide, writes down everything in it that they want to watch in prime time (8-10pm), and then the podcast is the discussion of their choices.

Name: The OkCupid Show
Description: Love scientists Amanda Sitko and Eli Newell guide a real dude through three real dates with three real ladies and it gets real weird. The OkCupid Show has been playing to sold out houses at the Upright Citizens Brigade Theater in Los Angeles for the last four years and is finally making its way up to the Great NorthWest.

Name: The Dana Gould Hour
Description: Comedian Dana Gould takes a look at our world… through his eyes… for your benefit. Joined by fellow comedians and other interesting people with a focus on the weird and the real. Conversation. Music. Monologues.

Name: Hit the Books
Description: Comics who are educators and/or highly educated present their best material for graduated laughter.

Name: Brew HaHa: The Comedy Show Drinking Game
Description: One part comedy show, two parts drinking game, Brew Haha is an interactive mix of standup comedy and your favorite pre-party ritual. It's Saturday night, drink up.

Name: Late Night Boogie
Description: Festival favorites blow the roof off the tent for this late-night standup showcase.

Name: Late Night Boogie
Description: Festival favorites blow the roof off the tent for this late-night standup showcase.

Name: Keep Everywhere Weird
Description: Austin, Portland, Brooklyn... we get it. You're weird.

Name: Competitive Erotic Fan Fiction
Description: Comedians compete writing and performing Erotic Fan Fiction pieces, based upon their whims or audience suggestion. It’s really stupid. And dirty.

Description: Let comedians Phoebe Robinson & Jessica Williams delight you with this stand up show based on the popular blog of the same name with some of the best comics from around the country.

Name: Andy Kindler's Particular Show

Name: Baked with Brendon Small and Steve Agee
Description: Baked is an evening of music and comedy hosted by Brendon Small (Metalocalypse, Home Movies ) and Steve Agee (The Sarah Silverman Program, New Girl, Adventure Time) and an incredibly talented band. Comics are encouraged to perform in a musical capacity after a set of standup comedy.

Name: 7 Minutes in Purgatory
Description: What happens when a comedian doesn't know how the audience is responding? Seven Minutes in Purgatory challenges comedians to perform a seven minute set in a soundproof room while the audience watches a live stream of their set.

Name: The CrabFeast Podcast
Description: The CrabFeast is a podcast hosted by comedians Ryan Sickler and Jay Larson, with new episodes every Toozdee. Pull up a chair, grab a coupla cold ones and celebrate the things that Ryan and Jay love most — storytelling, family, friends and comedy.

Name: Sunday Dinger with Gabe Dinner
Description: Local funnyman and festival favorite Gabe Dinger hosts a closing show featuring some of the most exciting performers in the fest.

Name: Talk Show: The Game Show
Description: Beloved comedian Guy Branum hosts the ultimate test of banter in a thrilling combination of America’s two least respected television formats. Three guests face off to prove who’s the best talk show guest by plugging, name-dropping, and anecdoteing their way to victory.

Name: Roustabout
Description: We are turning over the reins to Kurt and the Norse Hall may never be the same. The only thing we know for sure is Roustabout will be full of surprises so be a part of the show everyone will be talking about tomorrow.

Name: Les Is More
Description: These ladies love ladies and you'll love them in this straight-up hilarious showcase.

Name: The Tinkle Twins!
Description: The Tinkle Twins stars Dana Gould (The Simpsons, Mob City) and Arden Myrin (Chelsea Lately, Orange Is the New Black) as douchey identical twins. The Tinkle Twins have no idea that the fact that they are a man and a woman, are different ages and have different parents would make it impossible for them to be exact replicas of one another. The Twins host a jacked-up fake kids show with stand up guests, characters and music.

Name: Boogie Down
Description: The finest standup showcase in the back of a burger joint this side of the Willamette.

Name: Dad's Favorite
Description: Witness the magic of Bridgetown as comedians from all over the country take the stage at My Father's Place.

Name: Late Night Open Mic
Description: The infamous Bridgetown Open Mic is back in a new location! You never know who will drop in and if they will stay fully clothed. Be there to witness the birth of Bridgetown legends.

Join Noah Gardenswartz as he hosts several of his favorite comedians fresh off of a huge smoke session. They'll bring the jokes and the snacks, you bring the laughter and awkward silence!

Name: Birthday Bunk Bash!
Description: Hey hey it's your birthday! Celebrate the comics who had birthdays during the festival plus many more as we close out the weekend with a bang.

Name: Hey Ladies!
Description: An amazing show featuring some of the funniest comics in the festival, who also happen to be women.

Name: Heart of Darkness
Description: Heart Of Darkness: a psychedelic showcase of comedy, live music and fringe scientists that has been a frequent Time Out New York critic’s pick, much loved by BrooklynVegan and hailed as ‘Excellent’ by The New Yorker.

Name: A Moment of Clarity
Description: Get on the wagon with our favorite comics who can always be trusted to tell you what happened last night.

Name: The Mike Eagle Show/Secret Skin Live
Description: Open Mike Eagle is an L.A. based hip-hop artist. On Secret Skin, he and his guests examine what’s really going on behind the face that comics put on for the public. The in-jokes. The heavy stuff. The tour stories. The day-to-day struggles and absurdities of being a working comedian.

Name: Peace Out
Description: A divine night of standup culminating in a guided meditation with comedian Laura House.

Name: Meet Me in the Bathroom and Tell Me All your Secrets
Description: An incredible night of comedy, music, and gunplay hosted by Dave Hill and a surprise house band.

Name: Ron Lynch Presents: Crapshoot
Description:
Everything that happens on this show is put on a slip of paper, put in a hat, and an audience member pulls one out, and tells us what happens next! Guaranteed to be fun and entertaining. Prizes! Surprises!
See it once, SEE IT FOREVER!

Name: Festival Closing Show
Description: A stellar lineup of comedians take the stage for one last hurrah!

Name: The Grawlix
Description: Join the three boys from Denver who are MEGA HUGE STARTS BUT STILL WITH HUMBLE ATTITUDES AND GOOD TIME VIBES, and their cast of comics for an evening of mile-high laughter.

Name: Guy Branum's Gay Bash
Description: Guy Branum brings family together for the biggest, gayest, merriest show of the fest.

Name: Funny Over Everything
Description: The original Funny Over Everything team is back together again with a blockbuster lineup. One of Portland's best produced shows has some of the nation's best comics.

Name: The K Ohle with Kurt Braunohler
Description: A live taping of the K Ohle's GET LOST format. The entire audience will be blindfolded, put on a bus and driven somewhere fantastic they've never been. During the bus ride they'll be entertained by Kurt and a special guest comedian taunting them the whole way. Once at this VERY SECRET LOCATION, they will be un-blindfolded and allowed to explore on their own, while Kurt explains where they are, and why they're there. The entire insane experience should take about 3 hours. Prepare for walking, and possible encounters with dirt and awe. Wear appropriate footwear.

Name: Kill Rock Stars Presents
Description:
Kill Rock Stars picked their favorite comics for this stand up show which is not to be missed!
*no rock stars were harmed in the making of this show

Name: Busted
Description: Walk both sides of the thin blue line with folks who have fought the law, been the law, or at least played the law on TV.

Name: New Negroes: Redux
Description: Back! And still Black! The New Negroes returns to attack the wackness mistaken for blackness. We again present a showcase of comedians from around the country that redefine and redesign. Come fux with the redux.

Name: Steven Wilber's Appropriately-Titled Comedy Show

Name: Imaginary Radio Program with Drennon Davis and Karen Kilgariff

Hosted by Luke Burbank (Wait Wait Don't Tell Me, Too Beautiful to Live), the show is taped in front of a live audience and airs on public radio stations around the country. Tickets

Join Comedy and Cocktails' favorite duo Jason Traeger and Brandy Feit along with host Brad Silnutzer and some Bridgetown favorites for this very special event.

For the Depressed, By the Depressed
